T*
(and in general \(some\) security people have been saying for years that once an attacker had) Tj
T*
(local code execution, the game was over. Our answer is that yes, we consider it a serious) Tj
T*
(security boundary, and if that situation ever changed we'd need a drastically different system) Tj
T*
(environment from our current environment . Our current environment has shared NFS fileservers) Tj
T*
(where people keep all their files and data , shared login servers for both general usage and) Tj
T*
(compute, a \(shared\) SLURM computer cluster , and a reasonably flexible shared web server) Tj
